<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="921" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d921">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115A Pacific War/486:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-22">June 22,
                                    1943</date>.<lb/>[Received June 23—2:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3716. American interests Japan. Department’s 1255 of May 25th.
                                Consulate, Shanghai, telegraphs: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>Japanese authorities now permit monthly payments interned
                                        civilians in form pocket money.</p>
                                    <pb facs="1038" n="1026" xml:id="pg_1026"/>
                                    <p>Have decided for present allocate 700 Nanking dollars to
                                        internees, equivalent about 40 Swiss francs per person
                                        monthly because insufficiency food at camps and constant
                                        depreciation currency. This amount probably soon requires
                                        increase.</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>